%bridge-context: Plain Blackwood (Aces); Gerber 4C over NT openings
{SOUTH is just shy of a 2\C opening bid, and when NORTH shows 13-15 points SOUTH 
wants to be in a slam.

SOUTH cannot use Blackwood because 4NT would be a natural invitation, but with NORTH's latest bid 
being 2NT he can use Gerber.

Two Major Aces and two Minor Kings fill the holes in SOUTH's hand so he bids 7NT.}

